Yes — you can stream a 25 GB (or 250 GB) GGUF straight off the disk and never hold more than a few megabytes in RAM.
The trick is memory-map the file and let the OS page in only the chunks you touch.
Below is a drop-in replacement for your current “load everything” routine that works on any Windows machine with any amount of RAM (as long as you have free disk space).
